{"id":14881643,"mediaExerciseId":"4b986f41-0463-4ffb-b9a7-504861cfea2f","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"18","chapterTitle":"Short-Term Finance and Planning","groupId":612438,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":633,"solutions":[{"id":6013424,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to determine the effective cost of borrowing.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Effective Cost of Borrowing** or also known as effective interest rate is the rate of interest that a borrower actually pays on a loan.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Effective Cost of Borrowing is computed as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{EAR} &= \\text{$\\bigg[1+\\bigg(\\dfrac{{i}}{{1-i}}\\bigg)\\bigg]^{m}$} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\nWhere:\n\nEAR - Effective Annual Interest Rate\n\n*i* - Discount Rate\n\n*m* - Number of Periods","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/e92973386f83ae8565cb6a60d3af1c77/lateximg_large.png","width":917},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/e92973386f83ae8565cb6a60d3af1c77/lateximg.png","width":459}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's identify the given figures in the problem.\n\n| | | \n|--|--:| \n|Average Collection Period |31 days | \n| Discount Rate|1.25% | \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/b22e80c8e1cafa4973b862e3d0729e32/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/b22e80c8e1cafa4973b862e3d0729e32/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"To begin, let's compute first the number of periods by dividing 365 days by the average collection period.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Number of Periods} &= \\dfrac{\\text{365 days}}{\\text{Average Collection Period}}\\\\[10pt]\n&= \\dfrac{\\text{365}}{\\text{31}}\\\\[10pt]\n&=\\underline{\\underline{\\text{ 11.7742 periods}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":285,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/d49db02c2a8620a9031e4b370e2d229b/lateximg_large.png","width":680},"regular":{"height":144,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/d49db02c2a8620a9031e4b370e2d229b/lateximg.png","width":339}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"We can now compute the effective cost of borrowing using the equation in step 3.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{EAR} &= \\text{$\\bigg[1+\\bigg(\\dfrac{{i}}{{1-i}}\\bigg)\\bigg]^{m}$} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[10pt]\n&= \\text{$\\bigg[1+\\bigg(\\dfrac{{0.0125}}{{1-0.0125}}\\bigg)\\bigg]^{11.7742 }$} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[10pt]\n&= \\text{$\\bigg[1+\\bigg(\\dfrac{{0.0125}}{{0.9875}}\\bigg)\\bigg]^{11.7742 }$} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[10pt]\n&= \\text{$\\bigg[1+0.0127\\bigg]^{11.7742 }$} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[8pt]\n&= \\text{$(1.0127)^{11.7742 }$} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{1.1596} -{\\text{1}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{0.1596 or 15.96\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\n**Therefore, the effective cost of borrowing is 15.96%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/da5eff7d1876cbf6df312ab26906ad9d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/13/d21a7198add35e556aaf78c236735041/da5eff7d1876cbf6df312ab26906ad9d/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"7f416085-5893-4c8c-a9cb-b1ba772190eb","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881644,"exerciseName":"8","page":633,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3f528392-caf4-4cd0-9253-65e6d5fc8fc3","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-questions-and-problems-8-3f528392-caf4-4cd0-9253-65e6d5fc8fc3"},{"id":14881645,"exerciseName":"9","page":633,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"245e463f-2288-4b82-a352-f602a20a4cd4","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-18-questions-and-problems-9-245e463f-2288-4b82-a352-f602a20a4cd4"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881642,"exerciseName":"6","page":633,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"72c0950c-1a0c-485f-83de-9fa80e79da05","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporat